{%- comment -%}
  main-coaching.liquid — body content for the Coaching page.
  Edit this file to update the page. No section editor in admin.
  SEO + JSON-LD live in snippets/seo-meta.liquid (context-aware via page.handle).
{%- endcomment -%}

<header class="hero short">
    <div class="container">
      <span class="eyebrow"><span class="dot"></span> Founder Coaching · $4K/mo · 10 slots</span>
      <h1>Two operators in your week.<br/><em>Every week.</em></h1>
      <p class="lede">Senior coaching for consumer-brand founders. Strategy, fundraising, product, growth, hiring, ops — the operating decisions you'll face at $0 to $5M. AI fluency comes along because that's how we work; it's not the pitch.</p>
      <div class="actions">
        <a class="btn ember" href="{{ routes.root_url }}pages/contact">Book a call</a>
        <a class="btn ghost" href="#what-we-cover">See what we cover</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </header>

  <!-- ============ WHAT THIS IS ============ -->
  <section class="section dark">
    <div class="container narrow">
      <div class="prose">
        <p class="pullquote" style="margin-top:0;">
          This is general startup coaching. Not AI training. Not consultancy retainer. Senior operators in the room every week, on whatever you actually need to talk about.
        </p>

        <p style="margin-top:32px;">We've built three businesses between us. Stix Golf — Series A and Series B, $100M+ in lifetime sales. Host Modern — $4.5M year one with a 10%+ profit margin. Influence Mobile — $200M+ lifetime revenue, third-largest mobile ad network in the world. Plus a venture studio's worth of innovation consulting at Prota Ventures (Exelon, ADP, Citi Bank). Plus Collin's coffee company. Plus a decade of creative-services work in Seattle before any of that.</p>

        <p>The coaching pulls from all of it. When you've got a question about whether to take a term sheet, we've taken term sheets. When you're deciding between a CMO hire and a Head of Product, we've made those calls. When you're sizing whether a new product line is worth pursuing, we have a framework for it — six pillars, weighted scoring — that we use ourselves.</p>

        <p>AI is woven in because every business we run uses AI as a leverage layer. If a question turns out to be "should I build a media-buyer skill for my growth team," we have an opinion. But most of the time, the question is more fundamental — and we treat it that way.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ============ WHAT WE COVER ============ -->
  <section class="section rule" id="what-we-cover">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-head">
        <span class="label">01 · What we cover</span>
        <h2>Whatever's load-bearing this week.<br/><em>That's the agenda.</em></h2>
      </div>

      <p style="font-family:var(--lf-serif);font-style:italic;font-weight:350;font-size:18px;line-height:1.55;color:var(--lf-graphite);max-width:720px;margin-bottom:48px;">
        You set the agenda each week. We bring the operator perspective, the relevant frameworks, and the honest read. Some weeks are tactical. Some weeks are strategic. Most are both.
      </p>

      <div class="row-list">
        <div class="row">
          <div class="num">TOPIC · 01</div>
          <div><h3>Strategy</h3></div>
          <div class="body">Positioning. Market timing. When to pivot, when to stay the course. Reading the competitive landscape. Choosing what not to do. The reframes that come from having watched several businesses navigate the same waters.</div>
          <div class="meta">Always relevant</div>
        </div>
        <div class="row">
          <div class="num">TOPIC · 02</div>
          <div><h3>Fundraising</h3></div>
          <div class="body">Pitch deck honesty (we'll redline yours). Target investor list. Term-sheet trade-offs. Board management before, during, and after the round. Whether to raise at all. We've raised, declined to raise, and watched founders get destroyed by the wrong investor on the cap table.</div>
          <div class="meta">Pre-seed → A</div>
        </div>
        <div class="row">
          <div class="num">TOPIC · 03</div>
          <div><h3>Product</h3></div>
          <div class="body">What to build next. What to kill. When to validate before investing. The six-pillar concept-evaluation framework we built at Stix. The hardest call most founders face — "do I keep going on this?" — done with structure, not vibes.</div>
          <div class="meta">Roadmap + validation</div>
        </div>
        <div class="row">
          <div class="num">TOPIC · 04</div>
          <div><h3>Growth</h3></div>
          <div class="body">Channel strategy, agency vs in-house, when to push spend and when to defend efficiency. Attribution honesty (Triple Whale, Northbeam, the gap between platform-reported and actual). The 2x growth posture frame from Stix.</div>
          <div class="meta">Acquisition + retention</div>
        </div>
        <div class="row">
          <div class="num">TOPIC · 05</div>
          <div><h3>Hiring &amp; team</h3></div>
          <div class="body">First five hires. Fractional vs full-time. How to interview operators (different from interviewing engineers). When to fire, how to fire. Comp structure for early stage. The team-design decisions that compound — for better or worse.</div>
          <div class="meta">First 20 hires</div>
        </div>
        <div class="row">
          <div class="num">TOPIC · 06</div>
          <div><h3>Operations</h3></div>
          <div class="body">Financial model sanity. Runway management. Supplier negotiations. Inventory planning. The boring infrastructure that decides whether the front-end can scale. Most founders avoid this until it bites; we'll help you avoid the bite.</div>
          <div class="meta">Backbone</div>
        </div>
        <div class="row">
          <div class="num">TOPIC · 07</div>
          <div><h3>AI fluency</h3></div>
          <div class="body">Where AI helps, where it isn't yet ready, how to think about which model for which job. Not the focus, but always available when relevant. If a question turns out to be "should I install a skill for this," we'll talk through whether it's worth doing now.</div>
          <div class="meta">Woven in, not the pitch</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ============ WHAT'S INCLUDED ============ -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-head">
        <span class="label">02 · What's included</span>
        <h2>Weekly working session.<br/><em>Plus async access between.</em></h2>
      </div>

      <div class="grid-3">
        <article class="card">
          <span class="num">INCLUDED · 01</span>
          <h3>60-minute weekly</h3>
          <p>One scheduled session per week, video. Same time on the calendar every week — we treat it as a non-negotiable hour. Both founders attend when relevant; one if the topic has a clear owner. You set the agenda 24 hours in advance.</p>
        </article>

        <article class="card">
          <span class="num">INCLUDED · 02</span>
          <h3>Slack between</h3>
          <p>Shared Slack channel with both founders. Async questions answered same business day. The "I'm walking into a board meeting in two hours, gut-check this" message is exactly the use case.</p>
        </article>

        <article class="card">
          <span class="num">INCLUDED · 03</span>
          <h3>Frameworks &amp; templates</h3>
          <p>Decks, frameworks, and templates pulled from our businesses, customized to yours as questions come up. Pitch deck templates. Concept-validation framework. Compensation worksheets. Whatever fits the question this week.</p>
        </article>

        <article class="card">
          <span class="num">INCLUDED · 04</span>
          <h3>Honest feedback</h3>
          <p>We'll tell you when the next product idea is wrong. When the hire isn't ready. When the round is too soon. When you're being unrealistic. Most founders have no one in their orbit who'll do this — that's the actual product.</p>
        </article>

        <article class="card">
          <span class="num">INCLUDED · 05</span>
          <h3>Network access</h3>
          <p>When relevant: warm intros into our operator network — funded founders, agency partners, fractional executives, recruiters. We don't trade intros for promised reciprocity; if it'll help you, we'll send it.</p>
        </article>

        <article class="card">
          <span class="num">INCLUDED · 06</span>
          <h3>Pause &amp; resume</h3>
          <p>Coaching can pause for a month if you need to disappear into a launch or a fundraise. Resume when you surface. Sixty-day notice if you want to end entirely. Month-to-month, no annual lock-in.</p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ============ PRICING + CAPACITY ============ -->
  <section class="section rule">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-head">
        <span class="label">03 · Pricing &amp; capacity</span>
        <h2>$4K a month.<br/><em>10 slots. We won't expand past it.</em></h2>
      </div>

      <div class="row-2col asym">
        <div>
          <div style="padding:32px 28px;border:1px solid var(--lf-rule);background:var(--lf-paper-deep);">
            <div style="font-family:var(--lf-mono);font-size:11px;letter-spacing:0.16em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--lf-mute);margin-bottom:14px;">Coaching</div>
            <div style="font-family:var(--lf-serif);font-weight:400;font-size:48px;letter-spacing:-0.025em;color:var(--lf-ember);">$4,000<span style="font-size:24px;color:var(--lf-graphite);font-style:italic;font-weight:350;"> /month</span></div>
            <div style="font-family:var(--lf-sans);font-size:14px;color:var(--lf-graphite);margin-top:16px;line-height:1.6;">Weekly 60-minute session. Slack access. Month-to-month, sixty-day notice. No annual contract. Paused months don't bill.</div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="prose">
          <p class="pullquote" style="font-style:normal;font-size:24px;color:var(--lf-ink);">The capacity cap is the product.</p>
          <ul style="list-style:none;padding:0;margin:24px 0 0;display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:14px;">
            <li style="display:grid;grid-template-columns:120px 1fr;gap:18px;align-items:baseline;border-top:1px solid var(--lf-rule-quiet);padding-top:14px;"><span style="font-family:var(--lf-mono);font-size:11px;letter-spacing:0.16em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--lf-ember);">Cap</span><span style="font-size:14.5px;line-height:1.55;color:var(--lf-ink-soft);">10 clients at a time. Both operators load your context before every weekly.</span></li>
            <li style="display:grid;grid-template-columns:120px 1fr;gap:18px;align-items:baseline;border-top:1px solid var(--lf-rule-quiet);padding-top:14px;"><span style="font-family:var(--lf-mono);font-size:11px;letter-spacing:0.16em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--lf-ember);">Waitlist</span><span style="font-size:14.5px;line-height:1.55;color:var(--lf-ink-soft);">When the 10 slots fill, we open a list. We don't expand past it — split attention degrades the work.</span></li>
            <li style="display:grid;grid-template-columns:120px 1fr;gap:18px;align-items:baseline;border-top:1px solid var(--lf-rule-quiet);padding-top:14px;"><span style="font-family:var(--lf-mono);font-size:11px;letter-spacing:0.16em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--lf-ember);">Duration</span><span style="font-size:14.5px;line-height:1.55;color:var(--lf-ink-soft);">Most run 6–12 months. Some shorter (around a fundraise). Some multi-year. All fine.</span></li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ============ FIT ============ -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-head">
        <span class="label">04 · Fit</span>
        <h2>Best for.<br/><em>And not for.</em></h2>
      </div>

      <div class="yesno">
        <div class="col yes">
          <h3>Best for</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Consumer-brand founders — DTC, omnichannel, retail-bound.</li>
            <li>Pre-seed through Series A. The $0 to $5M stage where every decision compounds.</li>
            <li>Operators who want a weekly check-in with people who've run the playbook.</li>
            <li>Solo or two-founder teams that need a third voice in the room.</li>
            <li>Founders in or near a fundraise — we've raised, declined, walked, and watched.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="col no">
          <h3>Where we'll say no</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Equity-only advisory arrangements.</li>
            <li>Co-CEO setups. We're booked running our own businesses.</li>
            <li>Companies above $10M revenue with installed-AI needs — take AI Implementation instead.</li>
            <li>Founders who specifically want AI training as the focus.</li>
            <li>B2B SaaS, deep-tech, healthcare, fintech — operator credibility doesn't transfer.</li>
            <li>A fifth slot. The cap is the product.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ============ DIFFERENCE FROM... ============ -->
  <section class="section sm rule">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-head">
        <span class="label">05 · How this is different</span>
        <h2>From advisors and fractional execs.<br/><em>Worth being explicit.</em></h2>
      </div>

      <div class="tile-grid">
        <div class="tile">
          <span class="num">vs · Equity advisor</span>
          <h3>Cash, cadence, outputs.</h3>
          <p>Advisors are part-time and their incentives diffuse. We show up on a schedule and earn the renewal each month.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="tile">
          <span class="num">vs · Fractional CMO / COO</span>
          <h3>Outside the execution layer.</h3>
          <p>A fractional is in your Slack daily, owning channels and KPIs. We coach the founder while the fractional runs the function. Often complementary.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="tile">
          <span class="num">vs · Group / accelerator coaching</span>
          <h3>1:1, no cohort, no homework.</h3>
          <p>Weekly. Wherever your business goes. No curriculum, no cohort, no asynchronous community.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="tile">
          <span class="num">vs · Executive coach</span>
          <h3>Coaching the business, not you.</h3>
          <p>Executive coaches focus on leadership patterns and personal growth. Useful work, different product. We sit inside the strategy and the model — operator-to-operator.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ============ CTA ============ -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="cta-block dark">
        <h2>Free 30-minute call.<br/><em>If we're a fit, you'll know in twenty.</em></h2>
        <div class="actions">
          <a class="btn ember" href="{{ routes.root_url }}pages/contact">Book a call</a>
          <a class="inline-link" href="{{ routes.root_url }}pages/implementation">Or see Implementation →</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

